"1146–1182":"1146–1182","1115–1167":"1115–1167","from 1161 to 1163":"van 1161 to 1163","1115":"1115","Abt 1145":"circa 1145","1146":"1146","1167":"1167","about 1115":"circa 1115","1175":"1175","about 1167":"circa 1167","about 1146":"circa 1146","1182":"1182","1119":"1119","Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, England":"Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England","Northhamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Horton, Northamptonshire, England":"Horton, Northamptonshire, England"},"en":{"about 1115–about 1167":"about 1115–about 1167","1119–1175":"1119–1175","1146–1182":"1146–1182","1115–1167":"1115–1167","from 1161 to 1163":"from 1161 to 1163","1115":"1115","Abt 1145":"about 1145","1146":"1146","1167":"1167","about 1115":"about 1115","1175":"1175","about 1167":"about 1167","about 1146":"about 1146","1182":"1182","1119":"1119","Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, England":"Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England","Northhamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom","Horton, Northamptonshire, England":"Horton, Northamptonshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Gobion","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Bhola, Boodram, Mohan, Narine, Parmanand, Pooran, Shiva.  French Andre, Marcelle, Pierre.","French: from a pet form of   Gobert  .","English (Lancashire): variant of   Gubbins  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Gobert","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Antoine, Marie-France, Monique.","French, German, and English (London): from a medieval personal name, <i>Godebert</i>, composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>gōd</i> ‘good’ or <i>god</i>, <i>got</i> ‘god’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. The name was popularized in England by the Normans, and probably absorbed an Old English form <i>Godbeorht</i>."]},{"name":"Goben","meanings":["Altered form of   Gobin  , a surname of English or French origin. In some cases however, the surname <i>Goben</i> (possibly of German origin; see 2 below) was changed to <i>Gobin</i>.","German (<b>Göben</b>): habitational name from Gobbin on Rügen Island (Pomerania) or perhaps from any of several places called Goben in Bavaria."]}]},{"name":"Hugh","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Hugues</i>, <i>Hugo</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>hug</i> ‘heart, mind, spirit’. It was originally a short form of various compound names containing this element. This was borne by the aristocracy of medieval France, adopted by the Normans, and introduced by them to Britain. It was consistently one of the most popular boys' names in the Middle Ages in England, but fell out of favour in the 16th century until it was revived in the 20th century. Little Hugh of Lincoln was a child supposed in the Middle Ages to have been murdered by Jews in about  1255 , a legend responsible for several outbursts of anti-Semitism at various times. The story is referred to by  Chaucer  in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Hugh Gobion I was born about 1115, in Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom. He married Abbess Matilda Of Barking about 1145, in Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. In 1161, his occupation is listed as sheriff of northampton in Northamptonshire, England. He died about 1167, in Northamptonshire, England, at the age of 54."},"et":{"about 1115–about 1167":"umbes 1115–umbes 1167","1119–1175":"1119–1175","1146–1182":"1146–1182","1115–1167":"1115–1167","from 1161 to 1163":"1161 kuni 1163","1115":"1115","Abt 1145":"umbes 1145","1146":"1146","1167":"1167","about 1115":"umbes 1115","1175":"1175","about 1167":"umbes 1167","about 1146":"umbes 1146","1182":"1182","1119":"1119","Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, England":"Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England","Northhamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Horton, Northamptonshire, England":"Horton, Northamptonshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1115–about 1167":"noin 1115–noin 1167","1119–1175":"1119–1175","1146–1182":"1146–1182","1115–1167":"1115–1167","from 1161 to 1163":"vuodesta 1161 vuoteen 1163","1115":"1115","Abt 1145":"noin 1145","1146":"1146","1167":"1167","about 1115":"noin 1115","1175":"1175","about 1167":"noin 1167","about 1146":"noin 1146","1182":"1182","1119":"1119","Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, England":"Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England","Northhamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Horton, Northamptonshire, England":"Horton, Northamptonshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1115–about 1167":"environ 1115–environ 1167","1119–1175":"1119–1175","1146–1182":"1146–1182","1115–1167":"1115–1167","from 1161 to 1163":"du 1161 au 1163","1115":"1115","Abt 1145":"environ 1145","1146":"1146","1167":"1167","about 1115":"environ 1115","1175":"1175","about 1167":"environ 1167","about 1146":"environ 1146","1182":"1182","1119":"1119","Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, England":"Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Angleterre","Northhamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Horton, Northamptonshire, England":"Horton, Northamptonshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Hugh Gobion I est né environ 1115, à Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a épousé Abbess Matilda Of Barking environ 1145, à Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. En 1161, sa profession de son indiquée est sheriff of northampton à Northamptonshire, Angleterre. Il est décédé environ 1167, à Northamptonshire, Angleterre, à l’âge de 54 ans."},"de":{"about 1115–about 1167":"um 1115–um 1167","1119–1175":"1119–1175","1146–1182":"1146–1182","1115–1167":"1115–1167","from 1161 to 1163":"von 1161 bis 1163","1115":"1115","Abt 1145":"um 1145","1146":"1146","1167":"1167","about 1115":"um 1115","1175":"1175","about 1167":"um 1167","about 1146":"um 1146","1182":"1182","1119":"1119","Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, England":"Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England","Northhamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom","Horton, Northamptonshire, England":"Horton, Northamptonshire, England","lifeSummary":"Hugh Gobion I wurde um 1115 in Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom geboren. Er hat um 1145 in Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom Abbess Matilda Of Barking geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn. 1161 ist sein Beruf als sheriff of northampton in Northamptonshire, England aufgeführt. Er starb um 1167 im Alter von 54 Jahren in Northamptonshire, England."},"ht":{"about 1115–about 1167":"about 1115–about 1167","1119–1175":"1119–1175","1146–1182":"1146–1182","1115–1167":"1115–1167","from 1161 to 1163":"from 1161 to 1163","1115":"1115","Abt 1145":"about 1145","1146":"1146","1167":"1167","about 1115":"about 1115","1175":"1175","about 1167":"about 1167","about 1146":"about 1146","1182":"1182","1119":"1119","Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, England":"Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, Angletè, United Kingdom","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England","Northh